%S A393993 0,1,3,4,6,8,10,13,16,19,23,27,32,35,41,45,52,57
%N A393993 Largest number of distinct slopes of lines determined by pairs of cell centers of a polyomino with n cells.
%C A393993 A slope is counted only once, even if there are several parallel lines with that slope.
%H A393993 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A393993/a393993.svg">Illustration of all optimal polyominoes for 1 <= n <= 18</a>.
%H A393993 <a href="/index/Pol#polyominoes">Index entries for sequences related to polyominoes</a>.
%F A393993 For n >= 3, a(n) >= n + max{A331781(k,n-1-k); 1<=k<=n-2}, realized by the polyomino with cell centers in (0,0), (x,1) for 0 <= x <= k, and (1,y) for 2 <= y <= n-k-1, for an optimal value of k. Does equality hold for all n >= 3?
%Y A393993 Cf. A000105, A331781, A393992 (distinct lines), A393994 (polycubes), A394393 (number of optimal polyominoes).
%K A393993 nonn,more,new
%O A393993 1,3
